claim: Recombinant HA antigens produced using BEVS have been shown to induce significantly higher levels of broadly cross-reactive antibodies against highly conserved regions of HA compared with egg-derived vaccines.
explanation: Table listing demographic and clinical characteristics (sex, race/ethnicity, coexisting illnesses, receipt of prior influenza vaccine) of participants receiving recombinant vaccine versus standard-dose vaccine does not support the claim: the table only presents baseline participant demographics and clinical characteristics and contains no data on antibody responses or cross-reactivity to conserved HA regions Note: Table is clear but provides no immunogenicity or antibody level data.
